    <!-- INSIGHT 2: Why is Bitcoin structurally different? -->
    <div class="insight-block">
      <h2 class="section-title">Not all money <span class="amber">leaks</span> in the same way</h2>
      <p class="prose">
        Every money has some form of supply expansion (though technically, in bitcoin's case it is more accurately described as issuance or perhaps emission). But the nature of that expansion &#8212; <em>who benefits, why it happens, and whether it can ever stop</em> &#8212; is what separates sound money from broken money.
      </p>

